# can't use real time data · pocketbase pocketbase · Discussion #233
created: 2022-07-27, last updated: 2026-04-16, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/233)

Why do you create the EventSource object on your own?
`client.Realtime.subcribe()` will take care for that.
You can check the examples from the Realtime docs - https://pocketbase.io/docs/api-realtime/.
Or in other words, the following should be enough:
```
import PocketBase from 'pocketbase';
const client = new PocketBase('http://localhost:8090');
// (Optionally) authenticate
client.Users.authViaEmail("test@example.com", "123456");
// Subscribe to changes in any record from "YOUR_COLLECTION"
client.Realtime.subscribe("YOUR_COLLECTION", function (e) {
console.log(e.record);
});
```
...
> **SSE events are send for create, update and delete record operations.**
> You could subscribe to a **single record** or to an **entire collection**.
> When you subscribe to a **single record**, the collection's **ViewRule** will be used to determine whether the subscriber has access to receive the event message.
> When you subscribe to an **entire collection**, the collection's **ListRule** will be used to determine whether the subscriber has access to receive the event message.

